His
father Yang said: 'I know he had been feeling under a lot of pressure 
with people constantly coming round demanding that he stop paying the 
money back but he just didn't have it and we couldn't afford to help him
any more. He had hoped to get a good job after graduating.'

He
said he had been unable to speak to his son since the stunt but he was 
hoping they could sort something out to remove the pressure.

He added: 
'If he kills himself nobody will get anything back, they just need to be
patient.'

Peng Hsieh is likely to be fined though for the stunt so they may have to wait a while longer than was planned.

